{"type":"message","id":"097a1969","parentId":"38d91034","timestamp":"2026-03-24T02:19:20.853Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_79n3zrwhpvbt_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 220909\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: the (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent state:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n- Key insight: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n- Next action: Implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier\r\n- Need to: Implement TIC classifier on pulse logs, measure invariant/variant classification, predict next pulse content\r\n\r\nWhat needs to happen:\r\n1. First, I need to understand what pulse logs exist and their format\r\n2. Then implement the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nLet me check what pulse logs exist and understand the format. I should look at recent pulse logs to understand their structure.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the goals more carefully:\r\n- Next action is TIC Experiment\r\n- Need to implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nI should first examine existing pulse logs to understand their format, then create the TIC classifier. Let me check what files exist in the logs directory.\r\n\r\nFor this pulse, I should:\r\n1. Read the most recent pulse log to understand format\r\n2. Create a TIC classifier implementation\r\n\r\nLet me start by examining the recent pulse log format, then create the TIC classifier script.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to unify Phase 1 and Phase 2. I need to examine the pulse log format first, then implement the classifier.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nExamine recent pulse log structure and create the initial TIC classifier implementation targeting `logs/pulse_*.md` files for the invariance/variance classification experiment.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Experiment: Test COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis\r\n# Success: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [string]$LogsDir = \"logs\",\r\n    [string]$OutputFile = \"research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n# Load pulse logs\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogsDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name -Descending | Select-Object -First 20\r\n\r\nif ($pulseFiles.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Host \"Insufficient pulse logs for TIC experiment (need at least 5, found $($pulseFiles.Count))\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"TIC Experiment: Analyzing $($pulseFiles.Count) pulse logs...\"\r\n\r\n# Extract content patterns across pulses\r\n# Invariant = appears in multiple non-consecutive pulses (causal structure)\r\n# Variant = appears in single pulse or consecutive clusters (ephemeral)\r\n\r\n$allContent = @{}\r\n$invariantPatterns = @()\r\n$variantPatterns = @()\r\n\r\nforeach ($file in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $file.FullName -Raw\r\n    # Extract key phrases (simplified - look for lines with specific markers)\r\n    $lines = $content -split \"`n\" | Where-Object { $_ -match '\\w+' }\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($line in $lines) {\r\n        $key = $line.Trim().Substring(0, [Math]::Min(50, $line.Trim().Length))\r\n        if ($allContent.ContainsKey($key)) {\r\n            $allContent[$key]++\r\n        } else {\r\n            $allContent[$key] = 1\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Classify: invariant if appears in 3+ pulses (non-consecutive equivalent)\r\nforeach ($pattern in $allContent.GetEnumerator()) {\r\n    if ($pattern.Value -ge 3) {\r\n        $invariantPatterns += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n            Pattern = $pattern.Key\r\n            Count = $pattern.Value\r\n        }\r\n    } else {\r\n        $variantPatterns += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n            Pattern = $pattern.Key\r\n            Count = $pattern.Value\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n$total = $invariantPatterns.Count + $variantPatterns.Count\r\n$invarianceRatio = if ($total -gt 0) { ($invariantPatterns.Count / $total) * 100 } else { 0 }\r\n\r\n# Output results\r\n$result = @\"\r\n# TIC Experiment Results\r\n**Date:** $(Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\")\r\n**Pulse Logs Analyzed:** $($pulseFiles.Count)\r\n\r\n## Classification Results\r\n- **Invariant Patterns:** $($invariantPatterns.Count)\r\n- **Variant Patterns:** $($variantPatterns.Count)\r\n- **Invariance Ratio:** $([math]::Round($invarianceRatio, 1))%\r\n\r\n## Top Invariants (Causal Structure Candidates)\r\n$($invariantPatterns | Sort-Object Count -Descending | Select-Object -First 10 | ForEach-Object { \"- $($_.Pattern) (count: $($_.Count))\" } | Out-String)\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria Check\r\n- **Classification Accuracy:** $(if ($invarianceRatio -ge 70) { \"PASS (>70%)\" } else { \"BELOW TARGET (<70%)\" })\r\n- **Next-Pulse Prediction:** PENDING (requires validation against next pulse)\r\n\r\n## Interpretation\r\n$(if ($invarianceRatio -ge 50) {\r\n    \"High invariance ratio suggests stable causal structure across sessions.\"\r\n} else {\r\n    \"Low invariance ratio suggests high variability - may indicate noise or novel content.\"\r\n})\r\n\"@\r\n\r\n# Write results\r\n$result | Out-File -FilePath $OutputFile -Encoding UTF8\r\nWrite-Host \"TIC results written to $OutputFile\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Invariance ratio: $([math]::Round($invarianceRatio, 1))%\"\r\nfile: scripts/TIC-Classifier.ps1\r\n```\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 22:09:46"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1197,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 220909\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations