{"type":"message","id":"57ff5c1e","parentId":"102d3755","timestamp":"2026-03-24T02:19:47.403Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_srbh51icmbef_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"experiments/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\n## Hypothesis\nCausal structure IS invariant structure - compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\n\n## Method\n1. **Parse** last 20 pulse logs from `logs/`\n2. **Extract** structural elements (headings, code blocks, bullet points)\n3. **Classify** each element as invariant (recurs ≥3 times) or variant (recurs <3 times)\n4. **Predict** next pulse content using invariant-only model\n5. **Validate** against success criteria\n\n## Success Criteria\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\n\n## Implementation Status\n- [x] Design complete\n- [ ] Parser: extract structural elements\n- [ ] Classifier: invariant vs variant\n- [ ] Predictor: next-pulse content\n- [ ] Validator: measure accuracy\n\n## Log Analysis\n- pulse_2026-03-23_220909.md: [to be analyzed]\n- ...\n```\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774318787399}}
